$interpreted: ？？？: Let's just hide the herbs in here, first...
Soohyeon: Alright, seems like everything is covered up... Now to go see mom. I wonder if she...
Soohyeon: Agh!
Soohyeon: It... it stopped... finally.
Soohyeon: But my body... it's like I'm losing more and more control.
Soohyeon: What if one day I... I totally lose it?
Soohyeon: No! That can't happen... why is it always me...
Maeok: Soohyeon? Is that you?
Maeok: Soohyeon?
Soohyeon: (I can't let mom see me crying)
Soohyeon: Mom~ I was just about to go see you!
Maeok: Didn't I tell you to stop coming to the Alliance Hall!? Really, there's all sort who come and go from here...
Maeok: Hm? Why are your eyes so red?
Soohyeon: Uh... I... I was reading a book last night. I guess I was up too late.
Maeok: Up all night again? Didn't I say...

Soohyeon: I know, I know... 
I should be like you, early to sleep and early to rise, so my skin can get nice and smooth...
Maeok: Are you mocking me? Hmph... well listen up—right now we have foreign diplomats in the hall. It's not a good time for you to be here.
Soohyeon: Oh yeah, the diplomats! I heard they came early!
Soohyeon: Don't worry, mom, I won't get in the way.
Maeok: Or... did you come because you were worried about me?
Bull Chieftain: Kong Maeok! Kong Maeok! Where'd you run off to!?
Bull Chieftain: Kong Maeok, did you delay the Martial Arts Tournament at the request of some foreigners!?
Bull Chieftain: Do you realize how important the tournament is to the Alliance? This is treason!
Qing Feng: It is not wise to be too hasty, chieftain. Why not let Kong Maeok explain herself, first? See if she is worthy of blame.
Bull Chieftain: Huh? That's not what you were just saying...
Qing Feng: Arbiter Maeok?
Maeok: My decision comes from the desire to uphold harmony between the Alliance, the Desert Kingdom and the Kingdom of the Sun.
Maeok: There is nothing I could have done. My hands are tied.
Qing Feng: Absurd! No one has been proven innocent or guilty here—why is it you who bends to their will, and not them to yours?
Maeok: Because...
Qing Feng: The tournament is of the utmost importance. Can't you understand that!? Have you completely lost track of what's important?
Maeok: I... Of course I understand how important the tournament is, but...
Wolf Chieftain: I bet she knows exactly what she's doing. Think about it—without the tournament, she could keep being the arbiter~!
Soohyeon: Excuse me? My mo—
Qing Feng: Arbiter Maeok, does he speak the truth? What are you scheming?
Maeok: Of course not, I have no ill intentions! I have devoted my life to this Alliance!
Qing Feng: Empty words! How can we trust you?
Maeok: Then let me prove my loyalty by stepping down, relinquishing my title.
Maeok: And my daughter Soohyeon will head the investigation into the diplomats' claims. When the tournament starts, she will not participate!
Maeok: You can be assured that, this time, no one from the Kyo Tribe will vie for the position of arbiter.
Soohyeon: Mom!
Maeok: Will this finally earn your trust?
Qing Feng: A bold proposition. We will have to discuss this further. Still, I can sense your loyalty, Kong Maeok.
Maeok: I'm so sorry for putting you in this position, Soohyeon.
Soohyeon: Mom, it's okay. You had no choice...
Soohyeon: (Mom... does she really want to step down?)
Soohyeon: (Maybe it's for the best. Less stress on her.)
Soohyeon: Eh? Is it that time already?
Yonghyeon: This time I'll win for sure! Say goodbye to Yonghyeon the boy—here comes Yonghyeon the man!
Yonghyeon: Agh! I still can't beat you!
Soohyeon: Don't get discouraged, you're still really strong.
Soohyeon: You're allowed to be strong and still lose sometimes.
Yonghyeon: That's easy for you to say, you won! Come on, let's go again!
Soohyeon: Nope, you can wait till next time~
Soohyeon: Anyway, win or lose, you'll always be a boy in my eyes~
Yonghyeon: Agh! Kong—Soo—Hyeon!!!
Yonghyeon: Huh? Isn't that the qilin chieftain? Why's he heading up to the Alliance Hall?
Soohyeon: (I wonder if it's because of yesterday...)
Soohyeon: Let's go check it out.
Soohyeon: Yonghyeon, you're not coming?
Yonghyeon: Ah... well...
Yonghyeon: It's just...
Yonghyeon: Those diplomat humans are all in there too, aren't they?
Soohyeon: So it's because you hate humans...?
Yonghyeon: Well, it's not my fault they're so disgusting!
Yonghyeon: No fur, no scales... they're just all weird and smooth, it's gross!
Soohyeon: Gross......
Yonghyeon: Yeah, super gross.
Soohyeon: ......
Yonghyeon: Why are you all quiet now? I wasn't calling you gross!
Soohyeon: Nothing... just... just thinking of something else...
Soohyeon: Then I'll go up on my own. I'm worried about mom... I'll see you later.
Yonghyeon: Ah, wait...
Yonghyeon: What's up with her?
Yonghyeon: I feel like she'd usually whine and make me come with her...
Soohyeon: Mister Toyokuni? Why is everyone here?
Toyokuni: ...Did you not notice? The Udumbara's flowers have bloomed.
Toyokuni: This morning.
Soohyeon: Oh wow... I guess I didn't look over that way today!
Toyokuni: I'm sure you're aware that after the east was split into three, the holy dragon became one with the earth, and only his wings remained.

Toyokuni: And from those wings sprouted the Udumbara tree. 
Do you remember what it means when its flowers bloom?
Soohyeon: Of course... It means the holy dragon has something to say to us. I wonder if it's about the tournament this time...
Qing Feng: Arbiter Maeok. Speaking for the East Alliance, I hope you do not disrespect the holy dragon's wishes any further with these requests.
Maeok: Ex... Excuse me? I thought you agreed to my terms yesterday?
Qing Feng: Ridiculous. Whether it be delaying the Martial Arts Tournament, or not allowing the Kyo Tribe's participation...
Qing Feng: Were these not all terms you put forward unilaterally?
Qing Feng: I had no say in any of it.
Maeok: Qing Feng, you...!
Seahorse Chieftain: Hmph, Kong Maeok, passing the blame again! I've personally memorized the holy dragon's instructions word for word.
Panther Chieftain: Aye, aye! Both chieftains are right.
Panther Chieftain: What the arbiter has suggested is against the holy dragon's teachings.

Panther Chieftain: The Udumbara has flowered as a warning! 
The arbiter must cease such selfish decision-making!
Turtle Chieftain: Darn tootin'! Our people were surprised as all get-out to see the Udumbara's flowers bloomin' at a time like this~
Wolf Chieftain: We had to calm them down, even though that should have been your responsibility, arbiter.
Shun: But, the Sun and Desert Kingdoms...
Qing Feng: It is Maeok's responsibility to deal with the foreigners. I, however, could not sit by and watch as our own people panicked. I had to consider their well-being.
Bull Chieftain: Qing Feng is truly a paragon of justice, one we should all aspire to!
Soohyeon: Ugh, mom can't even get a word in...!
Tokoyuni: The position of arbiter, if filled adequately, is quite a thankless job.
Himawari: I think we've made our case. Let the arbiter make a decision!
Bull Chieftain: Yeah, make a decision!
Ace: If this is the Alliance's choice, then I am gravely disappointed. It will surely strain our relationship and may force our kingdom's army into action.
Maeok: ...This... I will need to consider matters further...
Soohyeon: (What can I do? Is there any way I could help mom and make everyone else happy, too?)
Soohyeon: What if... if we let Ace stay here, temporarily?
Soohyeon: We can't delay the tournament, but we also don't have any extra manpower... So, let Ace stay here and investigate things himself.
Maeok: Ridiculous! The Udumbara is sacred! We can't just let a foreigner go poking around!
Maeok: This goes against all of the holy teachings!
Soohyeon: Foreigner, huh...
Soohyeon: Then... what if we give him temporary status... as a spectator?
Himawari: A spectator?
Soohyeon: Yes... He'll have official status during the tournament, and then he won't be a foreigner anymore.
Toyokuni: That's actually... not bad...
Soohyeon: But, Ace, if the tournament ends and you still haven't found anything, you'll have to leave and accept that the Alliance has nothing to do with the attacks.
Ace: ...I can accept that.
Maeok: But... do all representatives agree to these terms?
Qing Feng: As long as he does not go against the holy dragon's teachings, then I will allow it.
Maeok: ...Okay. Then the Martial Arts Tournament will go ahead as planned.
Soohyeon: Great! One less thing to worry about, mom!
